definition.value: This is an AE which is a rare endocrine condition featuring a low blood sodium concentration and dehydration in response to injury (trauma) or the presence of tumors in or surrounding the brain.
This is an AE which is a head injury that temporarily affects brain functioning.
This is an AE which is the pathologic process that results in an area of necrotic tissue in the brain (cerebral infarct) with embolic.
This is an AE which is a neurological condition characterized by encephalopathy, thyroid autoimmunity, and good clinical response to corticosteroids.
This is an AE which is a cephalic disorder in which the prosencephalon (the forebrain of the embryo) fails to develop into two hemispheres.

This is an AE which is the common collective name for human betaherpesvirus 6A (HHV-6A) and human betaherpesvirus 6B (HHV-6B) and can be associated with encephalitis in the case of immunocompromised patients.

This is an AE which is a syndrome (a set of signs and symptoms) with encephalomyelitis that is the consequence of cancer in the body, specifically due to the production of chemical signaling molecules (such as hormones or cytokines) by tumor cells or by an immune response against the tumor.
This is an AE which can result from neonatal encephalopathy and perinatal arterial ischaemic stroke, usually at term, but also in preterm infants.
This is an AE which is a form of white-matter brain injury, characterized by the necrosis (more often coagulation) of white matter near the lateral ventricles.
This is an AE which is a set of symptoms that may continue for weeks, months, or a year or more after a concussion – a mild form of traumatic brain injury (TBI).

This is an AE which is a neurologic disorder caused by exposure to neurotoxic organic solvents such as toluene, following exposure to heavy metals such as manganese, as a side effect of melarsoprol treatment for African trypanosomiasis, adverse effects to prescription drugs, or exposure to extreme concentrations of any natural toxin such as cyanotoxins found in shellfish or freshwater cyanobacteria crusts.

This is an AE which is a rare condition that is characterized by progressive damage (-pathy) to white matter (-leuko-) in the brain (-encephalo-), particularly myelin, due to causes such as exposure to substance use, environmental toxins, or chemotherapeutic drugs.
This is an AE which is a hyperacute and frequently fatal form of acute disseminated encephalomyelitis(ADEM).
This is an AE which is an acute inflammation of the protective membranes covering the brain and spinal cord caused by adenoviral.
This is an AE which is rare but well recognised entity usually manifesting 1-4 weeks after anoxic exposure and characteristic subcortical white matter demyelination with necrosis of globus pallidus.

This is an AE which is a structural defect in the cerebellum, characterized by a downward displacement of one or both cerebellar tonsils through the foramen magnum (the opening at the base of the skull).

This is an AE which is a motor disorder caused by damage to the brain (specifically the posterior parietal cortex or corpus callosum) which causes difficulty with motor planning to perform tasks or movements.
This is an AE which represents a complex category of disease with diverse immunologic associations, clinical manifestations, and therapeutic outcomes.

This is an AE which is a rare inflammatory disorder of the central nervous system,It may also affect the peripheral nervous system, and has features in common with both Miller Fisher syndrome and Guillain Barré syndrome.
This is an AE which is a rare and fatal autosomal recessive degenerative disorder that causes progressive damage to nerve cells and loss of white matter in the brain.
This is an AE which is a rodent-borne viral infectious disease that presents as aseptic meningitis, encephalitis or meningoencephalitis.
This is an AE which is an extremely rare cephalic disorder involving encephalomalacia.
This is an AE which is a rare condition in which parts of the brain are affected by swelling, usually as a result of an underlying cause.
This is an AE which is commonly associated with significant morbidity.

This is an AE which is a rare and often fatal viral disease characterized by progressive damage (-pathy) or inflammation of the white matter (leuko-) of the brain (-encephalo-) at multiple locations (multifocal).

This is an AE which is a rare inflammatory neurological disease, characterized by frequent and severe seizures, loss of motor skills and speech, hemiparesis (weakness on one side of the body), encephalitis (inflammation of the brain), and dementia.
This is an AE which is a common complication in septic patients and clinical presentation may range from mild confusion and disorientation to convulsions and deep coma.
This is an AE which is a rare benign disease that can cause myelopathy.

definition.value: This is an AE which is either caused by trauma including that arising from medical interventions or spontaneously sometimes in those with predisposing conditions.
This is an AE which is a rare form of chronic, progressive brain inflammation caused by slow infection with certain defective strains of hypermutated measles virus.
This is an AE which can present with a variety of sensory deficits that can be difficult to diagnose clinically because of their seemingly disconnected manifestations.
This is an AE which is an injury to the brain caused by an external force.

This is an AE which is a disease linked to the X chromosome and is a result of fatty acid buildup caused by a defect in the very long chain of fatty acids transporter in peroxisomes, which then causes damage to the myelin sheath of the nerves, resulting in seizures and hyperactivity.
This is an AE which means any disorder or disease of the brain caused by AIDs, especially chronic degenerative conditions.
This is an AE which is a communication disorder resulting in incoherent talkativeness.
This is an AE which is a closed sac on the pituitary, having a distinct envelope and division compared with the nearby tissue.
This is an AE which is the increase in the volume of pituitary tissue due to the enlargement of its component cells.
This is an AE which is tumors that occur in the pituitary gland.
This is an AE which is a pituitary mass of cells (tumor) that lacks the ability to either invade neighboring tissue or metastasize (spread throughout the body).
This is an AE which is characterized by the absence of a subjacent cerebral lesion and neurological or intellectual deficit.
This is an AE which is seizures which affect initially only one hemisphere of the brain.
This is an AE which is a group of non-communicable neurological disorders characterized by recurrent epileptic seizures.
This is an AE which is a single seizure lasting more than 5 minutes or two or more seizures within a five-minute period without the person returning to normal between them.
This is an AE which is common, particularly in the setting of medically refractory epilepsy.
This is an AE which is primarily a disorder of childhood.
This is an AE which is a neurological disorder that is characterized by brief, recurring seizures that arise in the frontal lobes of the brain, often while the patient is sleeping.
This is an AE which should be recognized as a discrete epileptic syndrome.
This is an AE which is a period of symptoms due to abnormally excessive or synchronous neuronal activity in the brain caused by hyperglycaemic .
This is an AE which is divided into simple and dyscognitive, with the latter resulting in the alteration of consciousness.
This is an AE which is the most common epilepsy syndrome in childhood.
